{{Quote|If you have to ask where I got it, you won't really want it.|Loh'khar the Finder|<ref name="The DarkStryder Campaign">{{DarkStryder|adventure=Turazza Eggs|book=The DarkStryder Campaign}}</ref>}}
'''Loh'khar the Finder''' was a [[Twi'lek/Legends|Twi'lek]] free-trader and procurement specialist. He was a member of the crew of the ''[[FarStar]]'' during its hunt for [[Moff/Legends|Moff]] [[Kentor Sarne]]. He had the uncanny ability to source virtually any item needed in a matter of minutes to a few hours, depending on the item.

==Biography==
===Early life===
Loh'khar claimed to have escaped from [[Ryloth/Legends|Ryloth]], fleeing a clan conspiracy directed against him. Acquiring a light freighter, he became a galactic salesman who imported and exported goods from countless planets. He would settle on planets and create buying networks to help him acquire the goods he needed, basing himself near urban centers of starports. Eventually, he would move on to another location and repeat the process.

During one such transaction, he acquired three [[Turazza]] eggs. The eggs hatched, and three Turazza sisters emerged and bonded with Loh'khar. Naming them [[Rizzal]], [[Vizzal]], and [[Nizzal]], the three sisters worked for him, running errands and collecting information.

During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], he profited from trading with both the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]]. He was responsible for assisting in the extraction of a Rebel infiltration team led by [[Thella]] from [[Kelada/Legends|Kelada]] by arranging transport off the planet via [[Platt Okeefe/Legends|Platt Okeefe]] and the [[Last Chance (YT-1300 light freighter)/Legends|''Last Chance'']]. Business was slower under the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], but not unprofitable. Trading out of his light freighter, Loh'khar stopped on [[Kal'Shebbol/Legends|Kal'Shebbol]]. He attempted to deal with Moff Sarne, only to have Sarne steal his freighter. Thankful for not being imprisoned, he set up a shop in the main starport, trading with the few freighter pilots who used the port.

===The ''FarStar''===
When the New Republic announced they were looking for a crew to man the ''FarStar'', Loh'khar applied to [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Judder Page/Legends|Judder Page]]. Page rejected him, feeling that he had no skills relevant to the mission. However, when he just happened to procure heavy-duty [[Turbolaser/Legends|turbolaser]] power capacitors that the ''FarStar'' needed, he managed to convince the New Republic his skills and diplomatic talents would be useful.

==Personality and traits==
===Nature===
Loh'khar kept tabs on everyone and everything. Through subtle manipulations, rumor-spreading and blackmail, he was canny at making arrangements behind the scenes while still appearing to be honest and noble. Confident and calm, Loh'khar arranged many deals simply to have people owe him favors that he would call on later.

===Relationship with the Turazza===
The three Turazza sisters bonded to Loh'khar as their "parent" and he raised them since birth. They were fiercely loyal to the Twi'lek, and acted as his messengers and agents in his dealings. Some said that they had even formed some type of telepathic or empathic bond with each other.

